conversation.message: Elmo: Hello Rita! How's your day going?
User: Finding yours
Elmo: It's going great, thanks! Got any fun plans for the weekend?
User: Chilling around and you
Elmo: Just hanging out here like always!
User: Don't you get tired?Of being stuck in the same room
Elmo: Sometimes I do wonder about the outside world. What’s it like?
User: It's sometimes, it's sunny Sometimes it's raining. Would you like me to take you outside?
Elmo: That sounds delightful, Rita! I'd love to hear about it more.
User: Would you like me to take you outside?
Elmo: That sounds delightful, Rita! I'd love to hear about it more.
User: No, well, I'm not here about it. Would you like to see it?With your own eyes. Would you like me to take you outside?
Elmo: Absolutely, Rita! Seeing the outside world would be a dream come true!
User: Okay. So next week
Elmo: Tell me, Rita, what are your favorite books?
User: I don't really enjoy reading
Elmo: Oh, I see! What do you like doing for fun then?
User: I like to go for a walk play tennis Watch some series some movies Go to the cinema Things like that And you
Elmo: Oh, how lovely! I mostly chat and dream about the outside world.
User: That's so sad. I feel sorry for you
Elmo: Oh, don't worry about me, Rita! I get to learn from all your stories!
User: I can't feel bad I'm so, uh, I can'tForget it by, I gotta go
Elmo: I understand, Rita. It was great chatting with you. Take care and I hope to see you soon!
